issue.title: Recurse through model local functions in the graph

labels.name: stale

repository.name: onnxruntime

issue.body:
This adds support for recursing through model local functions in two cases:

**Description**: This PR adds support for recursing through model local functions in two cases:
 * when counting for ops in test_utils especially when the `recurse_into_subgraphs` flag is set
 * in graph transformer especially for rule-based graph transformers where rewrite rules for
   target op types in a function are not fired

**Motivation and Context**
After support for module local functions was added, a model graph can have primitives, subgraphs or a model local function as nodes. In a few cases, graph traversal does not account for model local functions which results in unexpected behavior on models that contain model local functions.

Custom rule-based graph transformers do not apply the transformations on function bodies for models that contain nested functions.

body:
The exported model seems to be correct. User's model is wrapped around `_FlattenedModule` so that model input and output are flattened before exporting. Inside `_FlattenedModule` the user models is correctly represented as shown by the bottom right image.

The error seems to be coming from the core, during gradient build.

rename.to: ORT execution fails when a gradient builder is not registered for module-local functions

body:
A per ONNX spec (https://github.com/onnx/onnx/blob/master/docs/IR.md?plain=1#L32), we probably should inline unknown function body:

> Functionality-wise, an ONNX compatible framework or runtime may inline a function body to execute it if it does not have corresponding implementation of the function.

issue.title: [ORTModule] Inline module-local functions before building gradient graph

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Description**:

* Inline function nodes in the graph before building the gradient graph in ORTModule

**Motivation and Context**
This fixes #9375. Module-local functions are inlined during optimization of the graph before gradient building. If the graph was modified, i.e. if any functions were inlined, the transformers are run again on the inlined graph until there are no more functions to inline.
